column25: Activity Type (not in the drop down list/choose from the list here: http://www.activityhero.com/in/san-jose-ca/categories)

column11: Playball is a sports and movement program for children age 2-6. We offer a multi-skill program which focuses on the basic fundamental sports skills of 6 different sports including soccer, tennis, baseball, basketball, hockey, and volleyball. Our creative and highly engaging curriculum ensures that the children have a positive experience with us and enjoy every minute of being physically active!

Our soccer academy is open to all children looking to develop their skills and to prepare for competitive soccer the program is led by our Director of Coaching - Jose Cedeno - supported by professional coaches from the club. Through the Academy program Children develop a wide range of fundamental soccer skills including dribbling, passing and shooting. earning is achieved through fun, exciting and motivating games and exercises, all participants will gain confidence, a positive self-esteem, increased motor skills and increased ball familiarity.

The Piedmont Soccer Club offers the PSC Youth Academy during the fall season for U8-U10 players and for parents and coaches of all age groups. The Academy is a series of clinics intended to help develop exciting, skillful players and to help develop more effective parent coaches. This will be done through an active learning environment where passion for the game and fun are the emphasis. The Academy is a recreational program that provides soccer skills training for 6, 7, 8 and 9 year olds and coaching education for interested parents that emphasizes fun for all participants.

Heritage's Year Round Academy is open to boys and girls ages 4 to 9yrs old. The Academy focuses on basic soccer skills under the supervision of our adept instructors with many years of club and high school experience.  Our Professional Staff will direct the natural talent of the children and guide them in a very progressive and detailed way.  Our goal is to teach them correct soccer fundamentals, how to make proper Soccer moves, and to form a team ideology.  Most importantly, its lots of fun!

BOCA is a competitive soccer club for boys and girls in the Sacramento area. Our club is dedicated to teaching the skills and tactics of the game with the idea of developing a constructive style of play based on fluid possession and team orientation. We believe that the athletic development of our youth must contribute to the development of good character and citizenship.

Soccer2gether has a vision to bring people together and create community through the great game of soccer. We are eager to develop soccer skills as well as life skills through exercises and games that engage our players in a variety of physical activities. Our program is focused on instilling basic motor skills, soccer fundamentals, self-confidence, and the virtues of teamwork and cooperation in a relaxed, unhurried and personal environment.

SFF Soccer Cubs is a fun-filled development program built to get your little ones out on the field for some quality playtime. Using a variety of activities, we help kids build confidence, improve coordination skills and learn soccer basics in a fun and safe environment. We’ve got classes for all ages from 18 months to 5 years – join the team!

We aim not only to improve your child's soccer skills but to provide a fun, non-competitive environment for our young grasshoppers to grow into confident and successful soccer stars of the next generation.  Through our techniques even the most shy and extroverted kids are able to excel at their own speed towards total skills development. ach clinic is designed to build upon the last to provide a comprehensive training experience in an enjoyable and supportive atmosphere. Grasshopper Soccer has a stellar reputation for our high instructor-to-student ratio to ensure each child receives the attention they deserve.
column33: San Francisco, Napa, and Marin locations

column11: Off The Wall in partnership with the Extreme Sports Academy is proud to present a variety of training sessions for area soccer and rugby players. We are excited to introduce a new age specific program for U5-U6 boys and girls.

Goalgetters Indoor Soccer takes place on a state-of-the-art indoor soccer field inside the Davis Athletic Club. The indoor facility allows everyone to play the world’s favorite game in comfort all year long. Our youth program starts kids young with a focus on having fun and learning life lessons such as respect, sharing, sportsmanship, teamwork and responsibility (all of which soccer caters to perfectly with its focus on teamwork, patience and fun for all). Meanwhile these little guys are getting the early skills to master the game later on. The older kids also have a ton of fun while benefiting from instruction based on European and Brazilian small-sided soccer. The indoor facility affords kids a high percentage of ball contact within a confined area. Also, for players who learn to play soccer indoors (with the emphasis on quick and accurate ball skills as well as on field vision and awareness), outdoor play becomes significantly easier.

Blues Player Development Clinics are geared towards the soccer player looking to increment their normal team training to build their skills and understanding of the game. These sessions are designed for players at all levels and also provide an excellent introduction into the Blues Training Philosophy. The U7/U8 Academy Program is the entry program into the Galaxy Blues competitive soccer team play and training. The program establishes necessary technical skills and confidence, while creating a thirst for personal challenges and individual improvement. Our program maximizes the players touches on the ball in a safe and friendly environment to encourage our young athletes to take risks and experiment. The technical skills and ability to function within small group concepts established in this program positions the young athlete to compete in the more competitive programs that follow.
column36: Player developement programs and player academy

column11: The purpose of our Skills Academy is to give youth soccer players opportunities outside their regular team practices to work on skill development and to help them understand the concepts of soccer and how it applies on the field. Sessions will be run by the Pacific Soccer collegiate coaching staff and players. Our training sessions run year round.

The Academy is designed for boys and girls who love soccer and are looking for developmental opportunities in addition to their practices with their fall team. The Academy is looking for players who are committed to developing their soccer skills and are mentally and emotionally ready to benefit from a structured technical training environment.

Cal South provides sanctioning as a CCAP Program in order to allow soccer instructors and youth players to participate in skills-based development programs with the resources and support of Cal South. CCAP Programs focus mainly on introductory soccer activities and/or technical skill development in an individual or small group setting. Advanced CCAP Programs may also offer specialty skill development training programs (goalkeeping, finishing, etc.). CCAP Programs predominately target U4 to U10 players, but may be offered up to the U19 age group. Participants are not provided a Cal South Player Pass, nor are they eligible for league play or tournaments unless appropriately registered and rostered to an eligible team.

The Brea Soccer Association (known on the field as AC Brea - referring to all levels of play, recreational, club, camps, clinics, futsal, adults, etc.) has a long history of service in and around the community of Brea. We are proud of our past and look forward to meeting the needs of our community. Today, AC Brea is a full-service youth and adult soccer organization.

At Little Rascalz our soccer classes for kids are unique and not like any other sports programs. hey are purposely designed to be fun, silly, age appropriate and a high energy experience for your toddler.  Our Soccer & Mommy 'n' Me sports programs feature exciting games and activities to teach the rudimentary skills of the sport, and all that comes with it. Your toddler will learn to participate in a group, follow simple instructions, cooperate with peers, develop gross motor skills, and lets not forget the obvious benefits of having them burn off some of that energy...eh! 
Little Rascalz Soccer coaches are, as you have come to know, highly experienced in dealing with toddlers and young children and are brilliant at what they do!  Located throughout San Diego, you can find us having fun at a community park in your neighborhood.

STRIKERS FC - SOUTH COAST is dedicated to provide a soccer program to regional youth that inspire enjoyment of the game, development of soccer skills and discipline of integrity. We offer a structured program that emphasizes discipline and sportsmanship. Family involvement is encouraged to help create a unified soccer community and support for the youth players. As players progress in skill and game understanding, expectations for team play can vary from player to player. STRIKERS FC - SOUTH COAST is dedicated to offering an empowering experience for all participants, with a focus on individual skill and awareness. STRIKERS FC - SOUTH COAST is also dedicated to develop players to their utmost potential.

FC Valencia is offering a variety of clinics, training camps, and recreation league activities geared towards player enrichment and overall development.  Creative Soccer Enterprises, Inc. promotes a vision of developmental soccer that advocates a unique focus of training and understanding of youth soccer. The principle objectives of Creative Soccer Enterprises, Inc. are to build programs that promote longer range, developmental and educational programs for youth soccer and beyond, but specifically based on the guidelines for learning that are endorsed by the United States Youth Soccer Association and the United States Soccer Federation.

column4: 374 E. H St. Ste. A PMB 441
column11: Our program provides the training and game exposure needed to build confidence in a fun filled instructional environment for boys and girls ages 4 to 10 years old. Players will learn: Ball Mastery, Coordination and most-of-all; HAVE FUN in a Positive Learning Environment. Some advantages to the program include small sided games for mastery, everyone plays, and most of all cultivates affection for the game of SOCCER.

Crescenta Valley Soccer Club’s First Kickers has teamed up with RightStart Soccer and founder Joel Govea to offer a special program designed just for young players. Our goal is to develop athletes with the skills and tools they need to be successful both on and off the soccer field. The program is age-appropriate and developmentally focused to encourage learning through technical demonstration and movement in a positive and fun learning environment. The purpose of the program is to develop players technically while building confidence and motivation, regardless of ability level.

The NHB Academy is designed to help players improve their technical skills and game tactics with an emphasis on ball control and technique. Sessions will be led by NHB licensed coaches under the direction of Academy Director, David Thomas and Director of Coaching and UCI coach Chris Volk. Players will receive small group training followed by small sided games, allowing players to practice and develop new skills.

Following a comprehensive review of elite player development in the United States and around the world, U.S. Soccer created the Development Academy in 2007 to improve the everyday environment for the elite youth player. he Development Academy is a partnership between U.S. Soccer and the top youth clubs around the country to provide the best youth players in the U.S. with an every day environment designed to produce the next generation of National Team players. The Academy’s programming philosophy is based on increased training, less total games and more competitive games.

LEARN SOCCER SKILLS & PLAY TEAM GAMES IN A FUN ENVIRONMENT - Our "JUNIOR ACADEMY PROGRAM" is LEARN SOCCER SKILLS & PLAY TEAM GAMES IN A FUN ENVIRONMENT - Our "JUNIOR ACADEMY PROGRAM" designed to develop players advanced technical skills. Each player is encouraged to have fun and develop a passion and loyalty to the beautiful game of soccer, while taking their technical game to the next level and developing tactical awareness. Our professional training staff will provide a fun and enjoyable experience while they focus on developing advanced technique in BALL CONTROL, DRIBBLING, PASSING, SHOOTING, TACKLING, TACTICS and PLAYING GAMES.

column1: Inland Empire Surf Soccer Club-Little Kickers
column11: nland Empire Surf Soccer Club announces the formation of its "Happy Kickers" program specifically designed for children aged 4-8 years old who are looking for a fun, high energy, positive hour of soccer! Our professional staff has planned a series of courses where young players can enhance their soccer skills while helping them with their overall growth, motor skills and confidence! The Happy Kickers courses are designed for children who are ready for a challenge while at the same time have fun with a group of children at his or her level. Classes are fun and fast paced while keeping the player focused on their balancing skills, coordination and teamwork! The Inland Empire Surf SC "Happy Kickers" program is held every Wednesday at the Surf Soccer Complex in San Bernardino.
column33: Surf Soccer Complex in San Bernardino

column11: SOCCEROPOLIS is a non-competitive introductory program which is designed to provide year-round soccer classes and camps for boys and girls ages 3 to 10. Children will learn the basic FUNdamentals of soccer such as: dribbling, trapping, passing, shooting, and play actual soccer games. This fast paced, energetic program will stimulate each child to build coordination, motor skills, balance and movement in a fun and safe environment. Our SOCCEROPOLIS program clearly understands the youth player and will certainly bring out their confidence and creativity through lessons taught on the field.

SoccerKidsUSA™ is a unique and playful children's fitness program that introduces boys and girls 2.5 – 6 years old to the wonderful game of soccer! With its fun and imaginative games and activities, SoccerKidsUSA™ helps kids develop their soccer skills, coordination, cooperation and learning abilities in a non-competetive environment. Young players are encouraged to listen, make choices, solve problems, and set goals in a supportive, motivating and positive atmosphere. Our nurturing and safe environment invites children to express their individuality while exploring our playing field of... "FUN, SUN & SOCCER!!!"
column33: Crestwood Hills Park, Cheviot Hills Park

column11: Soccer Kids America was founded in 2008. Our mission is to provide a fun and positive environment to assist kids in learning and developing soccer skills. Our programs are designed to support kids in learning to love the sport of soccer and to develop a positive self esteem along with a basis for future success in soccer and in life. We offer camps, classes, youth and adult soccer tournaments and futsal indoor soccer leagues for youth ages 4-17 years old.

Soccer Routes (Inc.) is a fun skill based, technical coaching company for kids (2-14yr). We offer professional coaching, which will challenge and develop children into better athletes and better people. Every week a different aspect of the game will be coached in Forty-five to Sixty minute sessions.

At Coast 2 Coast Soccer, we "Make Soccer Fun". We run after school soccer programs and day camps. We are now the largest after school soccer program provider in California & Texas. We partner with over 80 School Districts & 25 Community Based Organizations. We offer the best soccer programs because: 1) We hire and train college soccer players; and 2) We have a highly organized & fun soccer curriculum.

column1: For the Love of the Game- Soccer for Tots
column11:
Our specialized curriculum, designed specifically for this age group, allows kids to develop their soccer skills at their own pace without the pressure of games and competition. Our small group, non-competitive format encourages multiple touches
of the ball often missing in games, but essential for player advancement. Our weekly classes develop not only their soccer skills but also coordination, motor, social, listening, and communication skills.   We provide a structured yet FUN environment which is the perfect balance for your child to work on their skills while building their confidence.

Autobahn Soccer Club is a unique soccer development program designed to provide youngsters ages 3-18 with an opportunity to improve fundamental soccer skills in a fun and safe environment. Here at Autobahn Soccer Academy, we pride ourselves on playing as a team to produce imaginative, entertaining and skillful football. We take time to develop and nurture our younger players to ensure that they reach their full potential. By guiding players through our extensive training programs, we have produced many players that we are proud of.
column36: Reg fee is due as well as monthly fee. Multiple locations.

column11: We believe that the joy of playing should be at the forefront of learning soccer and that the development of soccer skills goes hand in hand with having fun, which is the foundation of our approach. Players learn the most through individualized attention, age appropriate challenges and positive reinforcement.  We are pleased to be offering Kidzkicks tot classes, youth clinics, league play, “days off” from school, private lessons and summer camp to youth ages 20 months-17 years.

The A to Z Soccer Academy is a children's soccer academy serving the communities surrounding Marina Del Rey, California. The Academy is a youth soccer school where kids learn the fundamentals of soccer in a fun, non-competitive, high energy environment. Our staff focuses not only on teaching the skills needed to play soccer but we also teach the meaning of teamwork and fair play. It is very important at the A to Z Soccer Academy that our soccer stars finish the academy having not only learned the fundamentals of soccer, but more importantly that they have learned to encourage each other, play together and help one another on and off the soccer field.
column33: The Campus at Playa Vista, Glen Alla Park, & Oceanview Park

column11: Sixteen years ago with a bag of soccer balls, a set of cranky plastic goals and 10 energetic four year olds, our program was born. And while things have grown a bit over the years, our approach to teaching has remained absolutely constant: keep it light, keep it moving, keep it fun. For our youngest kids in Soccer, we effectively disguise the sport’s basic skills in games – some classic, some created on the spot. Cookie, Star Wars, Mr. Wolf, Red Rover – all focus on dribbling, ball control, shooting, shielding… By the time the children are old enough for “competitive” soccer, they are comfortable with the ball and are ready to move on to greater challenges.

HappyFeet has a variety of programs to fit all children’s needs. All of our programs use our friendly "story time with a soccer ball" approach that has received recognition by many early education experts as the premier preschool-age fitness program. Happy Feet classes are 30 minutes in length (National Association for Sports & Physical Education recommendation). Every child constantly has a ball. HappyFeet uses nursery rhymes, songs, stories and fun games with a soccer ball to maximize motor skill development. Two and three year olds love acting out nursery rhymes and songs. Four and five year olds have a blast with stories and fun games.

The Brazilian Futebol Academy (BFA) is a premier soccer academy located at Qualcomm Stadium in San Diego. Our coaching staff is composed of top soccer professionals highly specialized in player development. Our partners include FIFA World Champion Cláudio Taffarel and Futsal World Champion Eduardo Valdez Basso.  BFA provides year-round training for all skill levels. We are not a club team; we are a player development academy that also welcomes club players who want to improve their game and reach their full potential. We apply a similar training methodology and philosophy used in Brazil at the youth divisions of professional teams. Our age-appropriate training integrates scientific and pedagogical methods combined with practical application experience led by specialized professionals. BFA offers soccer training on a year-round and seasonal basis for youth participants ages 7 – 17. A typical year-round schedule consists of two training sessions per week with an option to add a third session per week that focuses on specific skills and techniques.

Conteh Soccer Academy provides pro-level soccer training. Small group training gives the player an opportunity to work closely with the coach without feeling lost in the crowd. Each group training is tailored to the needs of the players and is focused on functional training. The player will learn how to effectively work with their teammates on the field. Private training is also available.

Clinics and group trainings at TCTC provide players with not only the physical practice of different technical, tactical and athletic abilities, but also the knowledge of why and how we do what we do to be a more educated soccer player. Skills clinics year round for all levels ages 7-14, and specialty clinics January through August for intermediate-advanced levels age 8-13 develop attacking, shooting, moves, defending, passing, speed, and more.  Take advantage of the unlimited clinic membership or the drop in rate for a single clinic.

Wherever your passion for Futbol lies, you'll find a class or program at the Futbol Factory to help you reach your goals on the fieldâ€”and enjoy every step along the way! Future Futbol players from 4 to 17 can improve their skills by enrolling in one or two weekly classes, held from 4 p.m. to 8 p.m. in our Control Room. Play for fun, develop your skills, and correct through repetitive actions. If you have the skills, you will play more, and no matter which team you're on, you'll be on the pitch all the time!
column36: Website says online registration coming soon

column11: 123 Private Soccer Training is designed to provide personal and educational correction to the individual to progress their soccer talent. When it comes to soccer, we believe that simplicity is genius.We at 123 PST can enhance players learning through our small group and individual soccer programs. The special benefits at 123 PST are that we specialize in individual instruction in weaker areas of a players’ game to accelerate their progress.

Southern California School of Goalkeeping (S.C.S.G.) began in 1996 in Southern California with a vision to provide opportunities for young goalkeepers to train, learn, and enjoy the position of goalkeeper. SCSG’s programs reach out to some 200 goalkeepers each year. From seven-year olds just learning the game, to 14-year-olds dreaming of playing for the U.S. National Team, to 18-year olds preparing for a college or professional career, goalkeepers of all abilities can benefit from our training model.

The Pre Academy is intended for players who want to take their soccer playing to the next level. The program replicates the methods used to train young players in the professional clubs of the U.K. Players with prior soccer experience who possess basic or advanced skills of dribbling, passing, and shooting are a great fit for this program. A Pre Academy class includes technical training, small group drills, and scrimmage.

For the past twenty years Go 4 Gold has been Northern California's Premier Soccer School, educating young girls and boys of all ages in a fun, positive environment. All students are evaluated by age and ability with training geared to maximizing their soccer ability. We offer group "academies" for goalkeepers and field players as well as private, one-on-one, instruction. All coaches are highly qualified professionals and are hand selected for their knowledge, personality and exceptional coaching ability.

Let you child’s first soccer experience be a great one! Designed specifically for children 3-8, Soccer and Smiles strives to teach the fundamentals of soccer in a fun, positive, non-competitive and safe environment, while promoting a love of the world’s most popular team sport! Children come away from our classes with self-confidence and a smile.

FYSC (Fremont Youth Soccer Club) and FYSL (Fremont Youth Soccer League) are dedicated to overseeing the soccer players of Fremont. We are based in Fremont, California and we are devoted to promoting the game of soccer and serving over 3,000 boys and girls in the Fremont area. We are affiliated with California North State Youth Soccer (CYSA), US Club Soccer, Norcal Soccer, the US Youth Soccer Association (USYSA), which in turn is affiliated with FIFA.  he Club Development Plan aims to provide the overall strategic framework for the development of our players, parents, coaches & club. Successful clubs have a well defined organizational structure, detailed player and coach development programs, and excellent administration.

Union City Soccer Club has been created for the purpose of providing our community members, youth and adults of all ages an environment free of violence, gangs and drugs to share in their love for Soccer be it full sided, small sided, indoor or sand we will also provide technical training and support for those individuals who aspire to pursue competitive or college levels of play . It will instill the value of continued and higher education, the importance of nutritional and physical health without prejudice to one’s age, race, color, gender, religion, national origin or economical milieu.

The Burlingame Soccer Club’s Academy Program is designed as an introductory soccer program for young boys and girls who enjoy playing the sport of soccer and who are looking to improve their soccer skills in an age appropriate FUN learning environment. This training can be taken in isolation or can be supplemental to any existing programs / teams (soccer or otherwise) that these young athletes maybe participating in.

The CVSC Recreational Program is for children ages 3-18. CVSC offers different programs for different age groups. Our youngest players participate in either the Bumblebee or Grasshopper Programs, which help teach the children and their parents soccer in a very family friendly environment. At these levels, it’s all about the basics of playing with ball. Our older players participate in our general recreational program, which is divided by gender and age groups from U7 to U19. In the younger age groups, skill development and fun is the still the focus. As the players mature, game results become more important for each team but fun should still be a focus of any game.

MCFC "Soccer Start" is a child-centered program that introduces young players to the world's greatest game and helps players develop technical skills . Each session includes movement games and skills activities that keep energetic kids running, and having fun. No sitting on the bench. Each player plays for the entire session.
column33: Robert Down Elementary School, Pacific Grove

column11: Big Kicks Soccer is a year-round co-ed program! Coach Lou created the program to teach the fundamentals of soccer to today's youth, while ensuring a happy and healthy environment. This program has been specifically designed to be taught at school campuses throughout the San Francisco Bay Area.

The aim of SoccerMainia programs is to aid each child’s development in three basic ways: physically, socially, and psychologically. All of these components can be developed in a fun-filled, safe environment. SoccerMainia is essentially a fun class of soccer skills and mini soccer games for boys and girls of all ages. When we schedule our classes, we group students by age, and when possible, level of experience in soccer.
